---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Reveal from '../components/Reveal.astro';
import RoleTable from '../components/RoleTable.astro';
import { siteConfig, t } from '../lib/i18n';

const locale = 'en';
const strings = t(locale);
const currentPath = Astro.url.pathname;

const roles = [
  {
    title: 'Urban Analyst & Scenario Designer',
    mission:
      'Define core urban challenges and translate engineering results into economic and policy conclusions.',
    background: 'Urban Governance & Design (UGOD), GIS, Public Policy (IPE), with interest in data analysis.',
  },
  {
    title: 'The Physicist:\nAtmospheric & CFD Modeler',
    mission:
      'Generate high-fidelity atmospheric data as the scientific backbone of the simulation.',
    background: 'Atmospheric Science (EOAS), CFD, Fluid Dynamics (e.g., WRF/Fluent), SEE.',
  },
  {
    title: 'The Brain:\nAI & Optimization Architect',
    mission:
      'Design dynamic path-planning algorithms that consume environmental data and output safe, efficient flight paths.',
    background: 'Data Science (DSA), Operations Research, Reinforcement Learning, ROAS, INTR.',
  },
  {
    title: 'The World Builder:\nDigital Twin & Simulation Specialist',
    mission:
      'Build the simulation environment and visualize results into an interactive digital twin.',
    background: '3D Modeling, AIGC, Robotics (ROAS), IoT, Computer Media & Arts (CMA).',
  },
];
---

<PageLayout
  title={strings.rbm.title}
  locale={locale}
  currentPath={currentPath}
  pageLabel="05 / RBM"
>
  <Reveal>
    <p>
      Recently, I'm dedicated myself to propose my <u><strong>RBM project</strong></u>.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>🚁 Project Title:</strong><br />
      Addressing the Economic and Operational Impacts of Adverse weather on Last-Mile Drone Logistics ⛈️:
      Building a Resilient Digital Twin for Urban Drone Logistics
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>🔭 Project Vision: From Go/No-Go to Intelligent, All-Weather Operations</strong><br />
      In the burgeoning <strong>Low-Altitude Economy (LAE)</strong>, the full potential of drone delivery
      is currently capped by adverse weather. This project moves beyond simple go/no-go decisions toward
      an intelligent, multi-layered digital twin for complex urban airspace.
    </p>
    <hr />
    <p>
      <strong><span style="color: red">📈 Project Update (Last updated: Sunday, Nov 30):</span></strong><br />
      Regrettably, the previously proposed project was not established due to insufficient staffing. I
      have currently joined a new RBM project led by
      <a href={siteConfig.social.scholarJi}>Dr. Yiding Ji</a>. I will update this homepage with details
      regarding the new project ASAP.
    </p>
    <hr />
    <p>
      <strong>End-to-End Validated Workflow</strong><br /><br />
      Our project is built upon a technically feasible workflow that transforms raw geospatial and
      meteorological data into a high-fidelity, interactive digital twin.
      <br /><img
        src="/assets/images/workflow_latitudinal.svg"
        alt="Workflow diagram"
        style="max-width:1400px; height:auto;"
      />
      <br />A detailed technical breakdown can be found in our
      <u>Feasibility & Toolchain Analysis report</u> (<a
        href="/assets/documents/Feasibility & Toolchain Analysis report (CN).pdf">中文</a
      >).
    </p>
    <hr />
    <p>
      <strong>🤝 Seeking Collaborators to Shape the Future of Drone Logistics:</strong><br />
      We are recruiting for the following roles:
    </p>
    <RoleTable locale={locale} roles={roles} />
    <hr />
    <p>
      <strong>💬 Interested in collaborating?</strong><br />
      Please feel free to <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.email}?Subject=Hello`}>contact me</a> if you are
      interested in my research.
    </p>
  </Reveal>
</PageLayout>
